Bundled third-party binaries (container image only)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The `transcode` container image does not merely depend on ffmpeg — it REDISTRIBUTES
prebuilt ffmpeg and ffprobe binaries, so it carries their licence and their source
offer with it.

  Component : ffmpeg + ffprobe (static builds carrying libx265, libsvtav1, libvmaf)
  Source of : https://github.com/BtbN/FFmpeg-Builds
  Build tag : autobuild-2026-07-13-14-11
  Version   : N-125573-g90436de5e1
  Licence   : GPL-3.0 (these are the "-gpl" builds — ffmpeg configured with
              --enable-gpl, which is what makes libx265 usable)

  Corresponding source: FFmpeg's own source is at https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg
  (revision g90436de5e1 above), and the exact build recipe — the configure flags and
  the pinned versions of every bundled library — is the BtbN/FFmpeg-Builds repository
  at the build tag above.

The Dockerfile pins that build by tag AND verifies the tarball's SHA-256 before
trusting it, so the ffmpeg in any given image is the exact one named here.

The ffmpeg binaries are invoked as separate programs (`exec`), not linked into the
`transcode` binary; `transcode` itself is AGPL-3.0-only and contains no ffmpeg code.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Go module dependencies are listed in go.mod and are fetched, not vendored; each
carries its own licence.
